  <Fragment slot="buying-guide">
    <BuyingGuideSection>
      <h2 id="buying-guide">Buying guide for AeroPress users</h2>

      <h3>Choose roast level based on the cup you want</h3>
      <p>If you want a cleaner, fruitier cup, lighter to medium roasts usually shine with AeroPress, especially on paper filters. If you want more chocolate, nuts, and body, medium-dark beans can be great too. The key is that darker beans often need a slightly coarser grind and a gentler hand, or they turn bitter fast.</p>

      <h3>Whole bean beats pre-ground if you want control</h3>
      <p>AeroPress is forgiving, but it still rewards fresh grinding. Whole beans let you adjust when a coffee tastes sharp, flat, or muddy. Pre-ground can work in a pinch, but it is like buying shoes in one size and hoping your feet change to fit them. If you brew often, a grinder is one of the most useful upgrades you can make.</p>

      <h3>Buy for your real routine, not your fantasy routine</h3>
      <p>If you travel, a manual grinder makes a lot of sense. If you brew half-awake before work, electric is usually the better call. If you love experimenting, get something with clearer adjustment control. If you just want a good morning cup with less fuss, the simplest grinder you will actually use is usually the best one.</p>

      <h3>Do not ignore freshness and storage</h3>
      <p>Stale coffee can make you blame the grinder when the beans are really the problem. Look for a roast date when you can, keep beans sealed, and only buy what you will use in a few weeks. If every cup tastes dull no matter what setting you use, the coffee may be tired rather than badly ground.</p>

      <h3>Know when it is worth paying more</h3>
      <p>Spend more when you care about cleaner flavor separation, easier repeatability, or better daily workflow. Do not spend more just because a grinder looks premium. AeroPress can make delicious coffee with modest gear. The goal is not to impress anyone. The goal is to make a cup you actually want to drink tomorrow morning.</p>
    </BuyingGuideSection>
